result.execSummary:
The defendant Allison R. Parnewicz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Allison R. Parnewicz appeared by zoom video from the Vilas County Jail.  Attorney Mary L. Roth Burns appeared by zoom video for Allison R. Parnewicz.  Attorney Dennis Brown in court for the State of Wisconsin.  State advised the court that the defendant would plea guilty to sole count, possession of methamphetamine.  Attorney Burns stated that her client would enter a no contest plea, so entered.  Plea questionnaire filed.  Rights given. Plea agreement accepted by the court and accepts the plea of no contest from the defendant and finds her guilty.  State recommends six month jail.  Attorney Burns wants her client to go to treatment in Massachusetts.  Court sentences defendant to six month jail with 119 days jail credit. Court costs of $518.00 to be paid within 60 days.  Payment plan can be obtained from the Clerk of Courts.
Plea/sentencing hearing on May 4, 2022 at 10:30 am.
